<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="269">
diagnosis A medium-sized reddish brown (major) or brownish yellow (minor) member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group distinguished as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="269">Major: head subquadrate; propodeal spine moderately long and suberect; postpetiolar node from above roughly trapezoidal; mesonotal convexity prominent and symmetrical in shape in both side and dorsal-oblique views; rugoreticulum extends as a broad band from the eye to the circular carinulae of the antennal fossa; frontal lobes completely covered by longitudinal carinulae; carinulae mesad to the eye reach halfway between the eye and the occipital border.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="269">
Minor: occiput narrow, with nuchal collar; humerus smoothly rounded in dorsal-oblique view. Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181716" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole aenescens Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole aenescens Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenescens">aenescens</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181717" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole alienata Borgmeier" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole alienata Borgmeier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alienata">alienata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181664" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole chrysops Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chrysops Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysops">chrysops</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33685" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cordiceps Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cordiceps Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiceps">cordiceps</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33704" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole dentata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole dentata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentata">dentata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181727" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole dione Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole dione Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dione">dione</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33720" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole eidmanni Menozzi" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole eidmanni Menozzi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eidmanni">eidmanni</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181805" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole midas Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole midas Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="midas">midas</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33896" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole nitidula Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole nitidula Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidula">nitidula</taxonomicName>
